  "statement": "# Reverse Bits\n\nReverse the bit order of an unsigned 32-bit integer.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: n = 43261596\nOutput: 964176192\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: n = 0\nOutput: 0\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: n = 1\nOutput: 2147483648\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Inputs are sized for local offline execution.\n- Return the value described by the method signature.",
  "editorial": "Use direct arithmetic, matrix indexing, or bit operations to preserve the required invariants while keeping extra state small.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def reverseBits(self, n):\n        out = 0\n        for _ in range(32):\n            out = (out << 1) | (n & 1)\n            n >>= 1\n        return out\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Watch fixed-width integer boundaries where the prompt requires them.",
    "For matrix mutation, mark or capture affected rows and columns before overwriting."
  ],
